DESCRIPTION:$0.00 - Tickets for the 8 PM screening of SIRAT 2025 • Moroc
 co\, France • 115 minutes • dir. Oliver Laxe Saturday\, March 28th at 
 Upland Wood Shop (354 W 11th St) FREE\, but ticketed | All Ages Showtime: 
 8pm *Sponsored by IU Arts &amp\; Humanities Council as part of Granfalloon
  2026. More info at grafalloon.indiana.edu . TRAILER Synopsis : Sirāt fol
 lows Luis (Sergi López)\, a father on a mission to find his missing daugh
 ter who was last spotted at a rave in the Moroccan desert. With his son an
 d their dog in tow\, the group find themselves immersed in desert rave cul
 ture and have to contend with the brutal landscape and hostile military pr
 esence in the region\, but not without some help\, cautious as it may be\,
  from a close-knit group of raver friends. As they venture deeper into the
  burning wilderness\, the journey forces them to confront their own limits
 . Sirāt is a powerful film\, bolstered by a powerful soundtrack by Kangdi
 ng Ray and led by an uncompromising directorial effort by Oliver Laxe. The
  Cicada crew saw this one at Heartland International Film Festival last ye
 ar and we've been working hard to bring this one to Bloomington\, so we co
 uldn't be happier to deliver this one free of charge in a fantastic venue\
 , the Upland Wood Shop free of charge with support by Granfalloon.
